"サーミ人はノルウェー北部、スウェーデン、フィンランド、西ロシア(コラ半島)の先住民と見なされています。更なる情報は<a "
"href=\"http://www.eng.samer.se/\">samer.se</a>、<a "
"href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sami_people\">\"Sami "
"people\"(Wikipedia英語版)</a>にあります。"

#. type: Content of: <h3>
#: ../../skycultures/sami/description.en.utf8:8
#: ../../skycultures/russian_siberian/description.en.utf8:28
#: ../../skycultures/tukano/description.en.utf8:43
msgid "Sources"
msgstr "出典"

#. type: Content of: <p>
#: ../../skycultures/sami/description.en.utf8:10
msgid ""
"Stellarium's Sami sky culture is based on the work of Bo Lundmark <i>Bæi'vi "
"mánno nástit</i> (Swedish title: <i>Sol- och månkult samt astrala och "
"celesta föreställninga bland samerna</i> [<i>Sun and Moon cult and astral "
"and celestial concepts among the Sami</i>], 1982), who based much of his "
"work on the writings of the Sami artist and author Johan Turi."
msgstr ""
"ステラリウムのサーミの星の文化はボー・ランドマーク(Bo Lundmark)の『<i>Bæi'vi mánno "
"nástit</i>』(スウェーデン語:<i>Sol- och månkult samt astrala och celesta "
"föreställninga bland "
"samerna</i>、サーミの人々の太陽と月の儀式、星と天の概念)1982年、を基にしています。彼の作品の多くはサーミの芸術家であり作家のヨハン・トゥリ(Johan"
" Turi)の著作に基づいています。"

#. type: Content of: <p>
#: ../../skycultures/sami/description.en.utf8:15
msgid ""
"This sky culture is a conglomeration of at least three slightly different "
"cultures from the people of the South-Sami, North-Sami and Russian Sami.  "
"Each of these groups have slightly different languages and as such there may"
" be small differences with some references."
msgstr ""
"この星の文化は南サーミ、北サーミ、ロシア・サーミの人々から成る少なくとも3つのわずかに異なる文化の集まりです。これらのグループはそれぞれ少しずつ異なる言語を使用しているため、一部の参照とは少し異なる場合があります。"

#. type: Content of: <p>
#: ../../skycultures/sami/description.en.utf8:19
msgid ""
"Sami constellations can be observed on Sami artifacts connected to the old "
"religion, suggesting that the night sky played an important cultural role "
"for Sami peoples in years gone by."
msgstr ""
"サーミの星座は古い宗教に関連する遺跡で観察できます。過ぎ去った年のサーミの人々にとって夜空が重要な文化的役割を果たしたことを示唆しています。"

#. type: Content of: <p>
#: ../../skycultures/sami/description.en.utf8:22
msgid ""
"The Sami sky culture has a lot in common with other arctic and sub-arctic "
"cultures in Eurasia. One unfortunate similarity is that much of the culture "
"was lost before it was recorded properly."
msgstr ""
"サーミの星の文化はユーラシアの他の北極圏および亜北極圏の文化と多くの共通点があります。残念な類似点の1つは、適切に記録される前に文化の多くが失われたことです。"

#. type: Content of: <h2>
#: ../../skycultures/sami/description.en.utf8:26
msgid "Constellations and Stars"
msgstr "星座と恒星"

#. type: Content of: <p>
#: ../../skycultures/sami/description.en.utf8:28
msgid ""
"The Sami constellations are probably very old but were recorded in writing "
"during the 19th century. In is unclear if the written record is complete. "
"The constellations and stars included here are all connected to the dominant"
" constellation, <i>Sarva</i> &mdash; the elk.  Sarva is the Sami name for "
"elk, an alternative name is <i>Sarvvis</i> &mdash; Bull elk.  The origin of "
"this constellation probably dates back to the old hunter culture before "
"reindeer were domesticated."
msgstr ""
"サーミの星座はおそらく非常に古いですが、19世紀の間に文書で記録されました。文書による記録が完全かどうかは不明です。ここに含まれる星座と星はすべて支配的な星座であるサルヴァ(<i>Sarva</i>、ヘラジカ)に繋がっています。サルヴァはヘラジカのサーミの名前です。代わり名はサルヴィス(<i>Sarvvis</i>、雄ヘラジカ)です。この星座の起源はトナカイが家畜化される前の古い狩猟文化にさかのぼります。"

#. type: Content of: <p>
#: ../../skycultures/sami/description.en.utf8:34
msgid ""
"<i>Sarva</i> consists of the Western constellations Cassiopeia, Perseus and "
"parts of Auriga. Constellations and stars surrounding Sarva represent "
"hunters of the elk.  <i>Favdna</i> (also transcribed as <i>Favtna</i>) is "
"the star Arcturus, and represents the Hunter who aims at the elk with his "
"bow and arrow (<i>Fauna davgge</i> &mdash; the Big Dipper).  Favdna must aim"
" well, for if he hits the Sky Support <i>Boahjenaste</i> (the star Polaris),"
" legend has it that the world will come to an end."
msgstr ""
"サルヴァ(<i>Sarva</i>)は西洋星座でカシオペア座、ペルセウス座とぎょしゃ座の一部になります。サルヴァを囲む星座や星はヘラジカを狙うハンターを表します。ファブナ(<i>Favdna</i>、<i>Favtna</i>とも表記)はアークトゥルス星のことで、弓矢でヘラジカを狙うハンターを表しています。弓矢はファウナ・ダブゲ(<i>Fauna"
" "
"davgge</i>)と呼ばれる北斗七星になります。ファブナは上手に狙う必要があります。彼が空の支えボアジェナステ(<i>Boahjenaste</i>、北極星)に当てた場合、伝説によると世界は終焉を迎えます。"

#. type: Content of: <p>
#: ../../skycultures/sami/description.en.utf8:41
msgid ""
"Favdna has a number of helpers: <i>Galla</i> (Procyon<sup><a "
"href=\"#note1\">1</a></sup>)  and his sons <i>Gallabarneck</i> (Orion's "
"belt), the \"Ski Runners\", <i>Cuoigahægjek</i> (Castor and Pollux) and "
"\"The Runner\" (Vega). The Pleiades are called <i>Rougot</i> (dog pack)  or "
"<i>Miese-cora</i> (calfpack)."
msgstr ""
"ファブナには多くの助手がいます。ガラ(<i>Galla</i>、プロキオン<sup><a "
"href=\"#note1\">1</a></sup>)、その息子ガラバーネック(<i>Gallabarneck</i>、オリオンのベルト)、スキー走者クオイガヘギェク(<i>Cuoigahægjek</i>、カストルとポルックス)と走る者(ベガ)。プレアデスはローゴット(<i>Rougot</i>、犬の集まり)やミエセ=コラ(<i>Miese-"
"cora</i>、幼獣の集まり)と呼ばれます。"

#. type: Content of: <p>
#: ../../skycultures/sami/description.en.utf8:46
msgid ""
"The Milky Way is called <i>Lodde-raiddaras</i> (lit. bird path) or <i>Jakke-"
"mærka</i> (lit. year mark).  The name used depends on the season. In the sky"
" chart of Johan Turi, one can observe a star <i>Guovso-naste</i>, morning "
"star, that can be identified as Venus, but this is not certain as it can "
"also be identified as Altair, a star showing the morning is approaching "
"(similar to Arcturus in the Norse skyculture)."
msgstr ""
"天の川はロッデ・ライダラス(<i>Lodde-raiddaras</i>、文語で「鳥の道」)やヤッケ=マエルカ(<i>Jakke-"
"mærka</i>、文語で「年の印」)と呼ばれます。ヨハン・トゥリ(Johan "
"Turi)の星図では、金星として判断できる星グウブソ=ナステ(<i>Guovso-"
"naste</i>、朝の星)を見ることができます。しかし朝が近づいていることを示す星であるアルタイルとしても判断できるため、これは確実ではありません(北欧の星の文化のアークトゥルスに似ています)。"

#. type: Content of: <p>
#: ../../skycultures/sami/description.en.utf8:52
msgid ""
"The Sami sky culture does not have a large number of constellations. This is"
" thought to be mainly because of the high Northerly latitude of the Sami "
"people's range.  Two factors contribute to this: that the Southern sky stays"
" below the horizon to a large extent, and that the Aurora Borealis is "
"frequently bright enough to obscure many stars."
msgstr ""
"サーミの星の文化には星座があまりありません。これは主にサーミ族の生活範囲の北緯が高いためと考えられています。2つの要因がこれに寄与します。南の空が地平線の下の大部分に留まっていること、そしてオーロラが頻繁に明るくて多くの星を覆い隠していることです。"

#. type: Content of: <ol><li>
#: ../../skycultures/sami/description.en.utf8:59
msgid ""
"<a name=\"note1\" />The exact star which represents <i>Galla</i> is "
"uncertain.  it is probably Procyon, Rigel or Sirius - Procyon was chosen as "
"Galla for this sky culture since Sirius is very hard to spot from the "
"latitude where the Sami live."
msgstr ""
"<a name=\"note1\" "
"/>ガラ(<i>Galla</i>)を表す正確な星は不明です。おそらくプロキオン、リゲル、シリウスのどれかですが、この星の文化ではプロキオンとしました。シリウスはサーミが住んでいる緯度から見つけるのが非常に難しいためです。"

#. type: Content of: <p>
#: ../../skycultures/sami/description.en.utf8:65
msgid "Jonas Persson (jonas.persson@physics.org)"
msgstr "Jonas Persson (ヨナス・パーソン、 jonas.persson@physics.org)"

#. type: Content of: <h2>
#: ../../skycultures/samoan/description.en.utf8:1
msgid "Samoan"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <p>
#: ../../skycultures/samoan/description.en.utf8:2
msgid ""
"Formerly known as the <i>Navigator Islands</i>, the Samoan archipelago has "
"been the launch site for countless ocean voyages since its settlement 3,000 "
"years ago by the ancestors of today’s Polynesians.  Like other Pacific "
"Islander societies, the Samoans possessed an incredible body of astronomical"
" knowledge, cultivated through generations of scientific observational study"
" (tofāmamao).  Over time, indigenous wayfinding science has been almost "
"completely replaced by digital navigation technologies, but the names and "
"stories attached to some celestial features have persisted through oral "
"traditions and colonial era publications. Beside their value as nautical "
"aids, the moon, stars, and planets also marked the lunar months, annual "
"socioreligious festivals, and the timing of agricultural cycles."
msgstr ""

